Joseph Stalin was a Soviet revolutionary and political leader who led the Soviet Union from the mid-1920s until his death in 1953. He rose to power as General Secretary of the Communist Party of the Soviet Union, becoming a Soviet dictator. Under Stalin, the Soviet Union became a one-party state, and he implemented sweeping economic, social, and political reforms. His rule is associated with the Great Purge, a period of mass repression and political repression in the Soviet Union. He is also known for his role in World War II, during which he ordered the invasion of Poland and the siege